div.div: 1. Lambda creates Redshift tables using Assume Role associated with the Redshift cluster.

div.style: font-size: 16px;

div.div: 2. Lambda creates and schedules an AppFlow flow to pull data from Google Analytics 4 to Redshift tables, including data mapping, filtering, and validation.

div.style: font-size: 16px;

div.div: 3. Scheduled processes in Redshift calculate, combine, and join data from Google Analytics 4.

div.style: font-size: 16px;

div.div: 4. The calculated data is unloaded to a cross-account S3 bucket.

div.style: font-size: 16px;

div.div: 5. An event in the S3 bucket triggers another Lambda function.

div.style: font-size: 16px;

div.div: 6. The triggered Lambda function processes the data in the S3 bucket for insights and reports in applications.

div.style: font-size: 16px;
font-size: 16px;
font-size: 16px;

div.div: - Event Bus and Rules: Used to manage the invocation of Lambda functions and other components.

div.style: font-size: 16px;

div.div: - EC2: Can be utilized for running the Lambda functions or other necessary components.

div.style: font-size: 16px;

div.div: - CloudWatch: Provides monitoring and logging for the various services in the workflow.

div.style: font-size: 16px;

div.div: - IAM Policy: Specifies the necessary permissions for data access and execution of services.

div.style: font-size: 16px;

div.div: - SAM Deployment: Utilized for deployment and management of the Lambda functions.

div.style: font-size: 16px;

These tools will allow you to create a visual representation of the workflow and its components, including the sequence of actions and interactions between them.
